# Frontend Architecture Rule

Build the application like it will grow beyond the current Figma frames.

## Preferred structure (Angular)

Separate concerns clearly:

- Pages/routes own layout and data orchestration (`src/app/pages/`).
- Feature components own domain-specific UI.
- Shared components own reusable UI patterns.
- Services and repositories own data access and side effects.
- Signals/computed values own reactive state where the codebase already uses them.
- Utilities own pure helper functions.
- Constants/config own static values.
- Design tokens live in `src/styles.scss` and Tailwind config.

## Component quality

Good components should be:

- Small
- Focused
- Reusable where appropriate
- Easy to name
- Easy to test
- Easy to remove
- Clear in their inputs/outputs
- Not tightly coupled to unrelated data

Use **Angular 18 standalone components** (no NgModules). Reuse `app-shell`, `nav-sidebar`, and existing page patterns.

## Extract components when

- A UI pattern appears more than once.
- A section is too complex inside a page.
- Logic can be isolated cleanly.
- A component maps to a real product concept.
- A visual pattern will likely appear again.

## Guardrails

- Do not create one giant component per screen.
- Do not prematurely abstract everything.
- Do not mix routing, API calls, formatting, and presentation in one component.
- Do not create generic components with unclear responsibilities.
- Do not duplicate design patterns.
- Preserve stable `data-testid` attributes on interactive elements.
